nts1.n: THE TIM & BARRY SHOW w/ Ian Mcquaid & Tim
nts1.d:
Tim & Barry have been documenting underground music since 2000. Journey from the latest UK drill back in time to classic grime and garage, all the way to afrobeats, dancehall and RnB. Expect the unexpected.
From the host: "The first half of  the show sees Ian pay tribute to Sly Dunbar" who passed on monday covering dub disco & dancehall from the legendary drummer. The second half of the show comes live from Tim's NYE 2025 set at Beneath the Baobab festival Kilifi Kenya ft Dennery, dancehall Abantone and more."

nts1.n: RADIO SUPER W/ ROSA PISTOLA - Bala VOL.I
nts1.d:
RADIO SUPER is Rosa Pistola’s show on NTS where she dives deep into the Latin American underground. Each episode zooms into different genres, scenes, and vibes, tracing their roots and evolution. It’s all about the sounds, the stories, and the pillars of the underground.
From the host: "La Bala is a subgenre of guaracha; it represents its dark, twisted side. This style was born in Colombia, in the coffee-growing region, in places like Cartago and Pereira. It is still a very new genre, and the producers shaping it are extremely young."

nts1.n: CLUB AEROBICS RADIO W/ BIANCA OBLIVION & KING DOUDOU (R)
nts1.d: "Special guest King Doudou blesses us with mix of all his own production--a signature blend of global club music including baile funk, reggaeton, bubbling + more. You'll also hear a preview of his collab with Bianca 'Teazerz,' coming out on LUCKYME 21st of Feb on her debut EP 'NET WORK'."

MOBBS chopping up whatever he finds

Cutting edge East African club sounds from Kampala's finest party starter.
From the host: "All that is new and good in electronic music from Africa and the diaspora"
Classic Jamaican records from the "Rocksteady Daddy" Asher G.

nts1.d: London & Istanbul based record label Zel Zele takes us on a monthly ride to earthly wonders and cosmic adventures. Bite the lip take the trip!
Organic soundscapes, field recordings and melodic ambience from composer Sophia Zhuravkova.

nts2.d: Where the wall meets the floor, Temporal Cove is a body of sound exploring the ethereal and ephemeral. Smilegoth dives into shoegaze, post-rock, house and more to articulate a flow of reverberations that can be felt on every surface.

Brian Weitz has been making music as Geologist with Animal Collective for going on two decades. The egg first cracked in the mid 90's at Baltimore record fairs and long overnight radio shows in New York on WKCR. Whether making sounds in the practice space or playing records, his bandmates call it the O'Brien System. One Tuesday each month you can go there with him on NTS 2.
From the host: "Companion mix/fraction of influences for my solo LP "Can I Get A Pack Of Camel Lights?" I had originally set out to write droney hurdy gurdy set but was deep in the SST catalog while listening to the You Don't Know Mojack podcast so tried something different and it became the new album. "
Forager Records is a Los Angeles based record label, committed to unearthing and breathing new life into rare and under appreciated sounds from the past.

nts2.n: Brown Acid Trippin' w/ Lance Barresi & DJ Tara Dactyl
nts2.d:
Life is short, have more fun. Lance Barresi of Permanent Records goes for all vinyl 45's, live and direct from the Los Angeles studio.
From the host: "An alphabetical journey through the Brown Acid Archives. All of these tracks come from real, vintage vinyl 45s from Hard Rock, Heavy Psych, and Proto-Metal artists beginning with the letter M!"

Blogger and playlister Omichive selects music from Asia, with a heavy focus on rock and alternative guitar sounds.
From the host: "This mixset is mostly composed of folk tracks, but it also includes songs in other styles. Even so, I believe they share a cohesive overall feel."

nts2.n: deadAir - Transmissions w/ Storm (fka Injury Reserve)
nts2.d: Radio live transmissions from the multidisciplinary and independent, deadAir & co. Come get shown the light!

nts2.n: Foreign Hour — Foreigner Live in March 2016
CDMX Tapes w/  TUFI & Romy Mats
nts2.d:
Mexican record label, Naafi, settle in at NTS for a showcase of the weirdest experimentations in club culture that have bubbled to the surface of Soundcloud. Dazed rhythms converging into Jersey stutters, and tumblr-era trap for two straight hours on a Monday.
From the host: _"Dj Fucci invites Romy Mats from Japan and Tufi from Argentina" _
ZULI, experimental club producer and VENT co-founder hailing from Cairo hits the NTS airwaves to showcase his club wares: aggressively left-field.
Shanghai, China collective 626 Company, headed up by Jackzebra deliver monthly broadcasts from the collective and their friends.

pop.soil is Lyra Pramuk’s bimonthly series exploring catharsis, transformation, and healing through sonic storytelling.
From the host "A one-hour mix of unreleased Lyra Pramuk material, these intimate sketches of devotional electronic vocals are rooted in techno, trance, dub, and gospel."

nts2.n: CONFUSING MIX W/ JOSH DA COSTA
NTS Guide to: LA Beat Scene (R)

subtle.d: Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
